From 1989 to 1995, Doctor Dré and Ed Lover were the co-hosts of MTV's hip hop music program Yo! MTV Raps.
The duo starred in the 1993 film Who's the Man?, directed by Yo! MTV Raps co-creator and co-director Ted Demme.
Dré and Ed Lover also recorded an album in 1994 titled Back up off Me!
Dré and Ed Lover participated in the 2003 Comedy Central Roast of their Who's the Man?
He appeared as a guest on MSNBC's The Beat with Ari Melber on June 1, 2018 along with Yo! MTV Raps co-host Ed Lover.
